{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_rigoletto_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280608798/1958062201/0403.xml":{"full_text":"'\"'Business\nAuchindoss to Open\nSpacious New Offices\nAuchlnclou. Parker it Redath. 21-year-old Waahlngton\nInvestment Arm. will start operations tomorrow In spacious\nnew offices at 1705 H street N.W.\nRecords and equipment were moved at the week's close to\nthe new site from 720 Fifteenth street N.W., where the Arm\nhas been located since 1042.\nThe attractive new offices will provide an additional 1.000\nsquare feet of space to meet\ncontinued irrowth. An unusu\nally large electric quotations\nboard will set a new style In\ncustomer convenience.\nElizabeth Draper of New\nYork developed lighting and\ndecorations for the new office\nEdwin Wethe was architect.\nAuchlnclou. Parker and Red-,\npath was organized In 1030 by\nHugh D. Auchlnclou and\nChauncey O. Parker. Jr., of\nWashington and Albert O.\nRedpath of New York The\nArm became a member of the\nNew York Stock Exchange In\nMav. 1031.\nFirst offices here were on the\nAfth Aoor of the National Sav- 1\nlngs St Trust Co. Building.\nOther offices were opened 'ater\nIn New York. Baltim )re, Phil\nadelphia. Wilkes-Barre. Beth\nlehem. Pa., and New Canaan.\nConn.\nIn addition to conducting a\ngeneral brokerage business, the\nArm is prominent in .he under\nwriting Aeld and It has been\nIdentiAed as prime underwriter\nN. Y. BOND SUMMARY\nFurnish** by Km tmcliM ertit LIST lIICLUDSS MOST ACTIVt ISSUSS\nHt\u00abh Low Clow Chi\nAlktC*s\u00abW Wi 8714 98>*+l>+\nAlice Lud cv 4a II 105'* 1041 4 104>*- 1' 4\nAllied I<+* 99>4 M\u2019< 98'+- AC\nAToa 4V..M 106>* IBt>* IWA-1\nAlcocr.cW 101V+100 100V4-I'*\nAlma Vk> w 101 99\u2019. 1001.- V*\nAlum!** an 4\"..nr 107 106'i 106'.- I*4\nAmn fan 3\" .*BB 101V* 994* 1004+-1\nAm AFP A. 2030 83>\u00bb 62'+-\nAm A -7t\u00abhr. 78 77 7744- \u201cA\nAm MAF cv V 77 110*4 109*. 109**\nAm MAF ev\u00abU*Bl U\u00bb U\u00bb 1 1544+34*\nAmTrtATcUar 117 110*4 110**-1\nAm TAT IH< 106 1 .105>+ 10