, who was\ntreasurer. Last night\u2019s exercises marked the 25th annual graduation\nexercises of the chapter.\u2014Star Staff Photo.\nGovernments\nMeet Losses,\nThen Rebound\nBy WARREN BENNETT\nAuocltttd Pus, Financial Writer\nNEW YORK. June 21.\u2014The\nUnited States Government bond\nmarket suffered its worst set-'\nback of the year this week.\nThe market rebounded some\nwhat on Friday but the week s\nlosses were severe and trading\nheavy.\nAs a result, corporate se\ncurities declined and new A\nnancing was hit.\nTwo factors inAuenced the\nsharp fall of governments.\nFirst was a heavy percentage\nof speculative interest in the\nTreasury\u2019s June Anancing Is\nsues.\nThe second factor was a\nrumor Thursday that the Fed\neral Reserve Board was about to 1\nshift from its \"easy money\u201d\npolicy. It was denied later, but\non Thursday losses ranged out\nto a full point.\nThe market rallied Friday on\nthe Federal Reserve's statement\nIt was sticking to its \"easy\nmoney\" policy.\nOVER COUNTER*\nThe following bid and asked prices\nare obtained from the National Asso\nciation of Securities Dealers. Inc., and\nother sources, but are unofficial They\ndo not represent actual transactions;\nthey are intended as a guide to the\napproximate ranee within which these\nsecurities could have been sold t indi\ncated bv the bid'i or bought (indi\ncated bv the \u2019asked* i at the time of\ncompilation (1? noon Friday) Origin\nof any quotation furnished on request\nVASHINOTON AREA LISTINGS\nBONDS Bid Asked\nFederal Storage :tg \u00ab7 75\nOiant FP db s\u2018as 71 _ 77 82\nGovt Empl Cp 5s 87 I I\nLincoln Service 5%s 87 I*B HH)\nMer.h Cred s d debs 8 88 I (HI\nMetro Inc cv db 8s 67 ill \u00bbm\nNat Press Bldg Inc 5s 79 74\nRaco et Club QAi E .\u2019is 65 75\nSo Oxv cv db 6* 86 uts 22\n8o Oxv cv deb fls 8M mu\nState Ln A Fin 5* Ho 100\nState \u2019AF cv deb 5s 69 141\nState LAF db 8s 77 ww 106\nSTOCKS\u2014\nAmer Mercury Insur 2 1 V\nAmer Sec At Tr Co uts 5o 63\nAnacostla National