l\nStreet Journal. I heeded ita\nwarnings. I cashed in on the\nideas it gave me for earning\nextra income and cutting ex\npenses. I got the money I\nneeded. Now I\u2019m slowly forging\nahead. Believe me. reading The\nJournal every day is a wonder\nful get-ahead plan.\nThis experience is typical.\nEach day The Wall Street\nJournal tells you about far\nreaching changes taking place\nin America. New inventions.\nNew industries. New way\u00bb of\ndoing business. New opportuni\nties to earn money. The Journal\ngives you quick warning of any\nnew trend that may affect your\npocketbook. The Journal is a\nwonderful aid to salaried men\nmaking $7,000 to $20,000. It is\nvaluable to the owner of a small\nbusiness. It can be of priceles*\nbenefit to young men who want\nto win advancement.\nThe Wall Street Journal ie\nthe complete business DAILY.\nHas largest staff of writers on\nbusiness and finance. The only\nbusiness pai>er served by all\nthree big presa associations. It\ncosts S2O a year, but you can\nget a Trial Subscription for\nthree months for sfi. Just tear\nout this ad and attach check\nfor $8 and mail. Or tell us to\nbill you. Address: The Wall\nStreet Journal. 44 Broad St,\nNew York 4. N. Y. w\n46 Get Awards\nAnd Diplomas i\nFrom ASLI\nWashington Chapter. Amerl-\ncan Savings and Loan Insti- j\ntute, conferred 46 certificates\nand diplomas at its 26th gradu- 1\natlon exercises at Hotel Shore\nham last night.\nWith more than 325 em\nployes and executives of area\nsavings snd loan associations\nin attendance. Max E. Lleur\nance. the Institute s national\nexecutive vice president, pre\nsented six graduate and 14\nstandard diplomas and 26\nachievement certiflratea.\nGraduate diplomas went to\nthe following: Roy M. Alex\nander. Vincent T. Mohler and\nM. Bradley Origgs of National i\nPermanent: Charles C. Elder\nkin. Perpetual: Winifred R.\nReumont, American Savings\nand Loan Association: James]\nP. Spelman. Enterprise Fed- ]l\neral.\nKarl E. Penner of District\nBuilding a